===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=ic|寻|巾|t1=two hands|t2=scarf}} - to wear a scarf. {{w|Shuowen Jiezi}} interprets it as {{Han compound|ls=psc|𠂤|巾|c1=p|c2=s|tr1=*C.tˤuj}}.

===Etymology===
Also written as {{och-l|率|to lead}}; both represent the ''s''-causative of {{och-l|律|to follow}}. Cognate with {{cog|bo|སྲིད||commander, leader}}.

For the surname, this is derived by removing a stroke of {{zh-l|師}}, which is the name of [[w:Sima Shi|Sima Shi]] ({{zh-l|司馬師}}), posthumously Emperor Jing of Jin ({{zh-l|晉景帝}}).

